      • getExecutionPosition

        public int getExecutionPosition()
        Get a hint about the execution order if multiple active recorder plug-ins are defined. Note: plug-ins with the highest execution position are executed at first for HTTP requests and at last for HTTP responses. If the method isAllowManualCallOnly() returns true then the execution order is never used.
        Returns:
        a hint about the execution order if multiple active recorder plug-ins are defined (can also be a non-unique number)
        See Also:
        isAllowManualCallOnly()
